{
  "texts": [
    "Despite their demonstrated use in biomedical sciences, large language models are just beginning to be adopted in ecology and evolution [1,15,53,54], and to our knowledge there is currently only one large language model, BiodivBERT, trained explicitly on biodiversity-related texts [53].",
    "Using language models in ecology & evolutionText mining is a broad domain with an array of approaches that can be used for the same tasks.",
    "Above we outlined three broad paradigms (Frequency-based, Traditional NLP, and Deep learning).",
    "While deep learning-based language models are revolutionary and an extremely active area of research, methods and tools from each of the three paradigms can be effective means to analyse text in ecology and evolution, even if not considered the current \"state of the art\".",
    "Often simpler rule-based tools can be more computationally efficient, and perform better for a specific task than a more general, probabilistic machine-learning based approach."
  ]
}